Sentencas: Cu-doped La1.7Ca0.3NiO4+delta has been synthesized and evaluated as potential intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode materials.
Titulo: Lattice structure, sintering behavior and electrochemical performance of La1.7Ca0.3Ni1-xCuxO4+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effects of Cu substitution for Ni on lattice structure, sinterability, electrical and electrochemical properties of La1.7Ca0.3NiO4+delta are investigated.
Titulo: Lattice structure, sintering behavior and electrochemical performance of La1.7Ca0.3Ni1-xCuxO4+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Cu-doping significantly enhances the sintering activity of La1.7Ca0.3Ni1-xCuxO4+delta.
Titulo: Lattice structure, sintering behavior and electrochemical performance of La1.7Ca0.3Ni1-xCuxO4+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: With increasing content of Cu, both the electronic conductivities and electrochemical performance remarkably increase, leading to an attractive cell performance.
Titulo: Lattice structure, sintering behavior and electrochemical performance of La1.7Ca0.3Ni1-xCuxO4+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The increased conductivity may be related with the elongated Ni(Cu)O-6 octahedron in perovskite layers while the decreased polarization resistance mainly correlates with the improved oxygen transport property induced by replacement of Ni by Cu.
Titulo: Lattice structure, sintering behavior and electrochemical performance of La1.7Ca0.3Ni1-xCuxO4+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Single cell test suggests that La1.7Ca0.3Ni1-xCuxO4+delta is a promising candidate for solid oxide fuel cell cathode.
Titulo: Lattice structure, sintering behavior and electrochemical performance of La1.7Ca0.3Ni1-xCuxO4+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell
